# Surface tokens: `field` vs `layer` (Carbon-style)

This DS follows the IBM Carbon surface model (`field-*`, `layer-01/02/03`,
`background-canvas`). Use these rules to decide which surface token to apply.

## The one question

**"Does the user type or pick a value inside this element?"**

- **YES → `field`** — it's a form-control surface.
- **NO → `layer`** — it's a container / chrome / overlay surface.

## `field` — interactive control surfaces

Use for the background of value-entry / selection controls:
inputs, textareas, selects/triggers, search boxes, checkboxes, radios,
date-picker triggers, choice tags.

Tokens are named by **state**, not by number:

| State | Token | Value |
|-------|-------|-------|
| default | `--rc-field-default` | `#ffffff` |
| disabled | `--rc-field-disabled` | `#fafafa` |
| hover | `--rc-field-hover` | `#fafafa` |

Rule: form controls hover with `field-hover`, NOT `layer-hover-01`.

Note: hover is intentionally the light one-step-from-white shade (`#fafafa`),
matching the white `field-default`. It equals the disabled surface value —
that's expected; the two are told apart by border + text color, not fill.

### Accepted exception — neutral buttons
Tertiary `Button` (incl. ai-tertiary) and `IconButton` intentionally use
`field-default` (hover `field-hover`) as their neutral control surface. This is a
deliberate extension of the `field` family to "neutral, bordered, interactive
control", not just value-input. Do NOT move these to `layer`.

## `layer` — container / chrome / overlay surfaces + elevation

Use for anything raised above the page background: cards, app header, side nav,
banners, menus, popovers, dropdown/select lists, calendars, panels, list rows.

| State | Token | Value |
|-------|-------|-------|
| base surface | `--rc-layer-01` | `#ffffff` |
| nested in layer-01 | `--rc-layer-02` | `#fafafa` |
| nested deeper / strong neutral | `--rc-layer-03` | `#eaeaeb` |
| hover (menu/list/card items) | `--rc-layer-hover-01` | `#fafafa` |
| selected item | `--rc-layer-selected-01` | `#eaeaeb` |
| active/pressed item | `--rc-layer-active-01` | `#eaeaeb` |

### Elevation model
The `layer` number encodes **nesting depth**, not an arbitrary shade:

- `background-canvas` (`#fafafa`) = the page background. It is **not a surface** —
  never place bare content directly on it; put a `layer` surface first.
- First container on canvas → `layer-01`.
- Container nested inside a `layer-01` surface → `layer-02`.
- Nested again / needs a stronger neutral fill (e.g. a badge, an icon box) →
  `layer-03`.

## Quick decision table

| Designing… | Token |
|---|---|
| input / textarea / select / search / checkbox / radio | `field-default` (disabled `field-disabled`, hover `field-hover`) |
| tertiary button / icon button | `field-default` (hover `field-hover`) |
| card / nav / modal / popover / dropdown / panel | `layer-01` |
| container inside a card | `layer-02` |
| deeper nesting / strong neutral (badge, icon box) | `layer-03` |
| hover on a menu/list/card item | `layer-hover-01` |
| selected list/menu item | `layer-selected-01` |
| page background | `background-canvas` |

## Don'ts
- Don't hover a form control with `layer-hover-01` (use `field-hover`).
- Don't put bare content on `background-canvas` — raise it onto a `layer`.
- Don't pick `layer-02`/`layer-03` by "which grey looks right" — pick by nesting
  depth.
- Don't hardcode hex (`#fff`, `#fafafa`, `#eaeaeb`) for surfaces — use the token.
